# Web App Structure (Next.js)

The main web application is located in the [web](mdc:web) directory. It is a [Next.js](mdc:https:/nextjs.org) project bootstrapped with `create-next-app`.

## Key Folders and Files
- **[src/app](mdc:web/src/app)**: Contains the main application routes and layout files. The entry point for the main page is [page.tsx](mdc:web/src/app/page.tsx) (if present).
- **[src/components](mdc:web/src/components)**: Houses reusable UI components, including subfolders for `ui`, `modals`, `editor`, and `oauth` components.
- **[src/hooks](mdc:web/src/hooks)**: Custom React hooks for state and logic reuse.
- **[src/lib](mdc:web/src/lib)**: Utility libraries and integrations (e.g., Stripe, Line Pay, authentication, business hours, Taiwanese zip code logic).
- **[src/types](mdc:web/src/types)**: Shared TypeScript type definitions.
- **[public](mdc:web/public)**: Static assets such as images and favicons.
- **[prisma](mdc:web/prisma)**: Database schema ([schema.prisma](mdc:web/prisma/schema.prisma)) and SQL views ([views](mdc:web/prisma/views)).

## Configuration
- **[package.json](mdc:web/package.json)**: Project dependencies and scripts.
- **[next.config.ts](mdc:web/next.config.ts)**: Next.js configuration.
- **[tsconfig.json](mdc:web/tsconfig.json)**: TypeScript configuration.
- **[README.md](mdc:web/README.md)**: Project overview and getting started instructions.

See also: [Project Structure Guide](mdc:web/README.md)
